value.idea: 73% of enterprise software projects fail. Companies waste $260 billion annually on software that never gets used. The average enterprise has 900+ SaaS applications but employees actively use only 40% of them. IT departments spend 30% of their time managing software licenses for tools nobody wants. Shadow IT is rampant because official channels are too slow. This isn't just inefficiency; it's existential. Companies are drowning in tool sprawl while their competitors move faster.

We have working prototypes achieving 1.2 Tbps throughput on commodity hardware.
